  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The transformation of neuroscience from a closed to an open science, where the entirety of research products like data and code produced during a study are routinely made available, has accelerated in recent years.",
    "Data sharing requires that the necessary human and technical infrastructure be in place to make these data broadly available.",
    "The first Human Brain Project,",
    "Maaike M. H. Van Swieten, Netherlands Comprehensive Cancer Organisation (IKNL), Netherlands funded by the US National Institute of Mental Health in the 1990s, launched some of the first efforts to \"database the brain, \" envisioning a \"paradigm shift in which primary data are openly shared with the worldwide neuroscience community\" (Koslow, 2000).",
    "Despite this early optimism, neuroscience had a rocky history with open data sharing."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
